Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel half the @garlic cloves{4}. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the potatoes and peeled garlic to the water and cook until just tender, ~{12-14%minutes}.

About 5 mins before the potatoes are ready, drain the @fish pie mix{1%pack} and add the fish to the pan. Simmer until the fish is cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

While the potatoes cook, pop the remaining garlic (unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, then scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel in your oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}. Zest and quarter the @lemon{1} into wedges.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing with the juice of half the lemon. Season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{}.

Quarter, core and thinly slice the @apple{1}(quartered, cored and thinly sliced) (no need to peel). Add it to the lemon dressing, then set aside.

Once the potatoes and fish are cooked, drain and allow to steam uncovered for ~{2%minutes}. Return to the pan, off the heat.

Mash together with a #potato masher{}, ensuring the mixture isn't too smooth so that some small chunks of potato remain.

Stir in the @wholegrain mustard{17%grams}, cheese, @breadcrumbs{50%grams} and salt and a pinch of lemon zest. Season with pepper and mix together.

Allow the mixture to cool slightly, then shape into 2cm thick patties, 3 per person.

Transfer the fish cakes to a large, lightly oiled #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{24-26%minutes}. Carefully turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, once the roasted garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the roasted garlic and the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

A few mins before the fish cakes are ready, pop a #small frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%grams} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} to the bowl of apple and dressing. Toss together.

Share the fish cakes between your plates. Serve with the apple salad, peas and garlic aioli alongside, as well as any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!